---
import Button from '../Button.astro';
---

<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-gradient-to-br from-storehouse-50 via-storehouse-100 to-emerald-50">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900">
        There's a reason this works.
      </h2>

      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-slate-600">
        Storehouse is built on a simple belief:
      </p>

      <blockquote class="mt-8 text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-display font-semibold text-storehouse-700 italic">
        "The space between your income and your spending is where freedom lives."
      </blockquote>

      <p class="mt-8 text-lg text-slate-600">
        We call it margin â€” and it changes everything. When your priorities are handled first, what's left isn't leftovers. It's permission.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-slate-700 font-medium">
        Most financial apps are about control. Storehouse is about peace.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10">
        <Button href="/philosophy" variant="ghost" size="lg">
          Read Our Philosophy
          <svg class="ml-2 w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5L21 12m0 0l-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
          </svg>
        </Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
